<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5831/132</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-11">October 11,
                                        1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Swedish Minister called and delivered to me a memorandum, of
                                which the attached is a copy,<note n="17" xml:id="d607fn17"><hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi></note> relating to proposed trade
                                agreement negotiations between our two governments. I thanked him
                                and replied <pb facs="0821" n="721" xml:id="pg_721"/> that I and my
                                associates would give the subject matter of his memorandum the
                                fullest and most careful attention and consideration.</p>
                            <closer><signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>